                                     GEOSAT

   [geosat_sat.gif]

Description

   The U.S. Navy Geosat radar altimeter satellite delivered data from
   April 1985- Sept 1989 covering the earth's surface between +/- 72 deg
   latitude. The first 18 months of the mission, referred to as the
   geodetic portion the satellite was in a 135-day repeat orbit and
   produced dense coverage of the ice sheets. The next 3 years the
   satellite was in a 17-day exact repeat orbit producing less dense
   ground coverage.

   More detailed description

